node.text: Solidarity for @mcdonalds workers and survivors. Advocates and survivors both, you can call the National Sexual Assault Hotline at 800.656.HOPE (4673) for help. Thank you for fighting such a difficult and important fight.
#بالييييز فولو🙆🏼‍♀️💚

For too long, @mcdonalds has refused to take seriously its workers' allegations of sexual harassment, That's why we're joining the fight, and filing charges to demand accountability on behalf of these brave workers. #MeToo
AHAHAHAHAHA!!! Holy shit! That picture is Hilarious!!!😂

The government is scared of the women in this country. We are a force! A large force. They keep attacking us as they didn’t come out of a woman! Respect our bodies, we won’t stay silent anymore and we won’t let them rule over our bodies! ❤️❤️
LOL.  Yeah...I’m sure it’s just rampant. I ain’t sayin’ @aclu_nationwide a gold-digga, but it ain’t filin’ on no broke nigga. 😂😂😂. Hos will be hos.

My sister works at McDonald’s and this guy was harassing her and she told her managers and they didn’t do jack shit. He was pushing her and tripping her in attempt to flirt and she almost tripped into the frying station. She requested that they never work the same schedule and they just ignored her.
Stand with the workers!

Worst bosses I ever had to work for were women.
What has happened to humanity!

@efloresmalpica I just wished I knew that it wasn’t my fault that I shouldn’t have been shamed and embarrassed that it happened to me. And that the managers should of done something. I didn’t even know what to do or who to call. I was only 16 it was 2006.

@xopaulette_xo I feel you and I’m sorry this happened and continues to happen to many in the world. I support anything that could help stop these violent acts against women and children. Find strength in that you are not alone, that you are precious and loved, and we will not take one step back. God bless!
@efloresmalpica thank you

I was raped twice by a supervisor. It started with unwanted touching I told the manager and the manager did nothing except started scheduling me to work Saturday morning opening with him which was pretty much just him and me and one more person. I was only 16 I spoke up and the manager did nothing but make it worse. A couple years ago I tried to get an attorney to see if I can still file charges but McDonald’s said they had no record of me working there I had to give them my w2 forms. This happened in 2006 and the attorney Told me it was to late to do anything and not enough evidence because I took to long and those people might not even work there
Take on Colleges too! 💪🏻

Get real.....you just need some cash
